# AEGIS Sentinel — Frontend Dashboard README

## Overview

**AEGIS Sentinel v5.1 Frontend** is a cyberpunk-themed IoT control dashboard built with pure HTML/CSS/JavaScript. It connects to Firebase Realtime Database for live sensor data and Railway.app HTTP backend for sending control commands.

No build tools, no frameworks — just open the HTML file or deploy to any static hosting.

---

## Features

### Real-time Monitoring
- Live temperature and humidity from DHT11 (via Firebase WebSocket)
- Live gas concentration from MQ sensor
- Dual charts: temperature history + gas history (40 data points each)
- Fan/relay status with countdown timer
- Alarm/buzzer status with countdown timer
- Auto color-coding: green (safe) → orange (warning) → red (danger)

### Manual Controls
- **Auto / Manual mode** toggle
- **Fan toggle** (works in manual mode only)
- **Fan Manual OFF** — cancels the 20-second auto timer instantly
- **Buzzer Manual OFF** — cancels the 20-second buzzer timer instantly
- **Alarm Mute** toggle — silences buzzer without cancelling timer
- **Emergency STOP** — kills fan, buzzer, and LED instantly

### Dashboard
- System diagnostics: temp max/min, humidity, gas max, fan runtime, alarm count
- Alert history panel with timestamps
- Real-time event log (100 entries)
- Railway backend ping latency
- ESP32 online/offline detection
- Boot sequence animation
- Matrix rain background with CRT scanline effect

