## Architecture

```
ESP32 → Firebase /sensors  (every 1 second, realtime push)
         ↓
Frontend ← Firebase WebSocket  (instant update, no polling)

Frontend → Railway POST /control  (when user clicks a button)
           ↓
ESP32 ← Railway GET /control  (every 2 seconds)
```

- **Firebase** is used for sensor data because it uses WebSockets — the browser gets updates instantly when ESP32 writes new data, with zero polling overhead.
- **Railway** is used for control commands because it allows input validation, logging, and custom endpoints like `/history` and `/stats`.

